---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
import { getAffiliateCTA } from '../../config/affiliate-links';
---

<Layout title="AI Website Builders with Code Export (2025): No Lock-In">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: 'AI Website Builders with Code Export', description: 'Which AI builders let you export code? Framer (React), Dorik (HTML), Webflow, CodeDesign compared. Avoid vendor lock-in.', url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/categories/ai-website-builders-with-code-export' }} />

  <section class="bg-[#FFF8F0] py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black">AI Builders with Code Export:<span class="block text-[#F5521A]">No Lock-In</span></h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mt-6">Build with AI, export code, host anywhere. Avoid vendor lock-in.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Quick Ranking</h2>
      <div class="bg-orange-50 border-[3px] border-orange-400 rounded-xl p-6">
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Framer:</strong> React code export (9.2/10) - Best for developers</li>
          <li><strong>CodeDesign.ai:</strong> HTML/CSS export (8.2/10) - Cleanest output</li>
          <li><strong>Webflow:</strong> HTML/CSS/JS export (8.6/10) - Advanced features</li>
          <li><strong>Dorik:</strong> HTML/CSS/JS export (8.1/10) - Simple option</li>
        </ol>
        <p class="text-xs text-red-600 mt-4"><strong>Important:</strong> Wix, Squarespace, Durable, 10Web do NOT allow code export. You are locked into their hosting.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Top Picks with Code Export</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black">Framer</h3>
            <span class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full font-bold text-sm">React</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Best for Developers</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-4">Exports clean React code. Component-based, modern, maintainable. Perfect if you know React or want to learn.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-4">Requires React knowledge. Export on paid plans ($15+/mo).</div>
          {getAffiliateCTA('framer')}
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black">CodeDesign.ai</h3>
            <span class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full font-bold text-sm">HTML/CSS</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Cleanest HTML Export</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-4">Exports clean, semantic HTML/CSS. No framework dependencies. Easy to host anywhere or customize further.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-4">Best for non-developers who want clean code. Export on paid plans.</div>
          {getAffiliateCTA('codedesign')}
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-black">Webflow</h3>
            <span class="bg-[#F5521A] text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-full font-bold text-sm">HTML/CSS/JS</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Most Powerful Export</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-4">Exports production-ready HTML/CSS/JS. Advanced features like CMS content, interactions. Steep learning curve.</p>
          <div class="text-xs text-gray-600 mb-4">Expensive ($18-212/mo). Export on paid plans only. Complex but powerful.</div>
          {getAffiliateCTA('webflow')}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Why Code Export Matters</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">üîì Avoid Vendor Lock-In</p>
          <p class="text-sm">With code export, you can leave the builder anytime. Your site is yours. Without it, you're stuck paying forever or starting over.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">üåê Host Anywhere</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Exported code can be hosted on Netlify, Vercel, AWS, GitHub Pages, or any web host. More control, potentially lower costs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">‚öôÔ∏è Full Customization</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Exported code can be modified arbitrarily. Want a feature the builder doesn't support? Add it yourself.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Code Export Comparison Table</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full bg-white rounded-xl border-[3px] border-gray-200">
          <thead class="bg-gray-900 text-white">
            <tr><th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Builder</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Format</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Quality</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Min Plan</th><th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold">Best For</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Framer</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-blue-600">React</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Excellent</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$15/mo</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Developers</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">CodeDesign.ai</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">HTML/CSS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Excellent</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">TBD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Clean code</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Webflow</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">HTML/CSS/JS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">Excellent</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$18/mo</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Power users</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Dorik</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-green-600">HTML/CSS/JS</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-yellow-600">Good</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center">$15/mo</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm">Simple sites</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">The Code Export Reality</h2>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-[3px] border-yellow-400 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">‚ö†Ô∏è Code Export Requires Technical Skills</p>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p><strong>Choose code export if:</strong></p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You are a developer or comfortable with code</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need custom features builders don't offer</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want to host on your own infrastructure</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You are concerned about vendor lock-in</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3"><strong>Stick with builder hosting if:</strong></p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You are not technical</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You want the builder to handle everything</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You don't want to manage hosting</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You prefer convenience over control</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">No Code Export = Locked In</h2>
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-[3px] border-red-400 rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-2">üö® These Builders Do NOT Allow Export</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">Wix, Squarespace, Durable, 10Web, Mixo, Pineapple Builder - your site is hostage unless you keep paying.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-red-600">If you leave, you lose everything. Must rebuild from scratch. This is intentional vendor lock-in.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Recommendation</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">üë®‚Äçüíª For developers</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Framer for React export. Modern, powerful, maintainable code.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-green-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">üë• For everyone else</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Don't worry about code export. Builder hosting is fine for 95% of use cases. Most people who say they want export never use it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
